update actions
--------------

1. update links in tools/sources.where (or extend fetch.py with some screenscraping)
2. manual downloads, above
3. lots of juicy commands:

(cd "/Volumes/MyBook/fort" && tools/apt-mirror tools/UBUNTU-apt-mirror.list)
(cd "/Volumes/MyBook/fort" && tools/apt-mirror tools/DEBIAN-apt-mirror.list)
rsync -avz --delete rsync.xemacs.org::xemacsweb "/Volumes/MyBook/fort/next/xemacs"
(cd "/Volumes/MyBook/fort/next/django-book" && wget -m -k -p -np http://djangobook.com/en/2.0/)
rsync -av --delete ftp.funet.fi::internet-drafts "/Volumes/MyBook/fort/next/I-Ds"
rsync -av --delete ftp.funet.fi::rfc "/Volumes/MyBook/fort/next/rfcs"
(cd "/Volumes/MyBook/fort" && pypimirror --initial-fetch tools/pypimirror.cfg; pypimirror --update-fetch tools/pypimirror.cfg)
rsync -av --delete ftp.funet.fi::CPAN "/Volumes/MyBook/fort/next/CPAN/"
(cd "/Volumes/MyBook/fort/next/w3" && wget -m -k -p -np http://www.w3.org/TR/)
(cd "/Volumes/MyBook/fort/next" && python tools/fetch.py -s tools/sources.where)

4. mirror the git repo ojwb set up (in future, maybe in a [git] section in tools/sources.where)

